                            <comment id="15249947" author="slebresne" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2016 14:03:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Cell.validate()&lt;/tt&gt; was wrongly trying to validate the value for tombstone cells. It was almost never a problem as tombstone cells uses an empty ByteBuffer as value which almost all types accepts (due to legacy), but &lt;tt&gt;smallint&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;tinyint&lt;/tt&gt; being new types, they don&apos;t.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch is rather trivial and comes with some unit test for that &lt;tt&gt;Cell.validate()&lt;/tt&gt; method (patch against 3.0 but merge cleanly to trunk and there is clearly no difference between the 2 here so didn&apos;t bother running CI twice):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
&lt;table class=&apos;confluenceTable&apos;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th class=&apos;confluenceTh&apos;&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/pcmanus/cassandra/commits/11618&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;3.0&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th class=&apos;confluenceTh&apos;&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/job/pcmanus-11618-testall/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;utests&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th class=&apos;confluenceTh&apos;&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/job/pcmanus-11618-dtest/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;dtests&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15266256" author="blerer" created="Mon, 2 May 2016 09:10:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks for the patch.&lt;br/&gt;
For the record, the problem will have also affected &lt;tt&gt;date&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;time&lt;/tt&gt; types.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15266337" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 2 May 2016 10:18:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
